        "## Analyze Ratings Distribution\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Calculate the frequency and percentage of each rating (1 to 5 stars) and visualize this distribution using a bar chart to understand user satisfaction levels.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "14f0fa8d"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "First, I need to calculate the frequency and percentage of each rating, display them in a DataFrame, and then prepare to visualize this data with a bar chart using `matplotlib.pyplot` and `seaborn`.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 733
        },
        "id": "45fb8809",
        "outputId": "033f1355-3a75-4f4e-b195-743188c1dfa3"
      },
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate frequency and percentage of each rating\n",
        "rating_counts = df['Ratings'].value_counts().sort_index()\n",
        "rating_percentages = df['Ratings'].value_counts(normalize=True).mul(100).sort_index()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create a DataFrame for better display\n",
        "ratings_distribution = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'Frequency': rating_counts,\n",
        "    'Percentage': rating_percentages\n",
        "})\n",
        "print(\"Ratings Distribution:\")\n",
        "print(ratings_distribution)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Visualize the distribution of ratings using a bar chart\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
        "sns.barplot(x=ratings_distribution.index, y=ratings_distribution['Frequency'], palette='viridis')\n",
        "plt.title('Distribution of Ratings')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Rating')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "execution_count": 6,
      "outputs": [
